topic: History Workflow Series ("Ancient Rome explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for Ancient Rome
goals.2: Find all the Roman Dictators (return the IRI and the name of the dictator)
goals.3: Identify the BGP for Roman Empire and Roman Republic
goals.4: Return the IRI and the name of all Roman emperors killed by homicide (see "manner of death") and, for each killed emperor, return also the IRI and name of the killer, if present in Wikidata.
goals.5: Return the Roman emperors who killed another Roman emperor (the result set must a list of 4-tuples with killer IRI and label, and killed IRI and label).
goals.7: Find the wars (note that "war" and "battle" are not the same thing) participated by the Roman Empire (return IRI and name of the war).
goals.8: Consider all the wars participated by the Roman Empire. For each war return the number of related battles and the opponent (a war is composed of one or more battles) (the result set must be a list of 5-tuples war IRI, label, opponent IRI and label, and #battles).

name: 5356f64747

1.narrative:
write your final query
getting the BGP of Ancient Rome data via Julius Caesar
1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q1048 wdt:P27 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name WHERE { wd:Q1747689 ?p ?obj . ?p sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
output: Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names ID
execution_output: Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names ID

2.narrative: getting the roman dictators data via Julius Caesar
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name WHERE { wd:Q1048 ?p ?obj . ?p sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?person ?name WHERE { ?person wdt:P39 wd:Q236885 . ?person sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20

3.narrative: getting Roman Empire and Roman Republic data via Julius Ceasar- country of citizenship relation to country of citizenship-has parts relationship
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name ?region WHERE { wd:Q1048 wdt:P27 ?obj . ?obj wdt:P527 ?region. ?region sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name WHERE { wd:Q2277 ?p ?obj . wd:Q17167 ?p ?obj. ?p sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20

4.narrative: getting to homicide and killer data by "manner of death" and "killed by" relation of Julius Caesar.
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?deathcause ?killer ?name WHERE { wd:Q1048 wdt:P1196 ?deathcause . ?deathcause sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?person ?killer ?nameKiller ?nameEmperor WHERE { ?person wdt:P1196 wd:Q149086 . ?person wdt:P157 ?killer. ?person sc:name ?nameEmperor. ?killer sc:name ?nameKiller. }limit 20
execution_output: Anton Graf von Arco auf Valley

5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?killedBy ?sub ?emperorName ?killerName WHERE { ?sub ?p wd:Q842606. ?sub wdt:P157 ?killedBy. ?killedBy ?p wd:Q842606. ?killedBy sc:name ?killerName. ?sub sc:name ?emperorName. }limit 20

6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q202161 wdt:P31 ?obj. ?obj sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name WHERE { wd:Q198 ?p ?obj. ?p sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20

7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?wars ?name WHERE { ?wars wdt:P31 wd:Q198. ?wars wdt:P710 wd:Q2277. ?wars sc:name ?name. }limit 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?wars ?name WHERE { ?wars wdt:P31 wd:Q198. ?wars wdt:P710 wd:Q2277. ?wars sc:name ?name. }limit 20

8.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?participant ?wars ?opponent ?warname (count(?warParts) as ?numberOfBattles) WHERE { ?wars wdt:P31 wd:Q198. ?wars wdt:P710 wd:Q2277. ?wars wdt:P710 ?participant. filter (?participant != wd:Q2277) optional{?wars wdt:P527 ?warParts}. ?participant sc:name ?opponent. ?wars sc:name ?warname. } group by ?wars ?warname ?participant ?opponent limit 20

SELECT DISTINCT ?participant ?wars ?opponent ?warname (count(?warParts) as ?numberOfBattles) WHERE { ?wars wdt:P31 wd:Q198. ?wars wdt:P710 wd:Q2277. ?wars wdt:P710 ?participant. filter (?participant != wd:Q2277) optional{?wars wdt:P527 ?warParts}. ?participant sc:name ?opponent. ?wars sc:name ?warname. } group by ?wars ?warname ?participant ?opponent limit 20
